EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO FISH AND WILDLIFE -- HUNTING AND HUNTING SAFETY--WILDLIFE
KILLING CONTEST
***
1 This act would ban wildlife killing contests on both public and private lands in the state.
2 Penalties for violations for individuals start at five hundred dollars ($500) and increase for repeat
3 offenders. Penalties for businesses and organizations start at one thousand dollars ($1,000) and
4 increase for repeat offenders or while under license suspension.
5 This act would take effect upon passage.
